EU continues to hesitate on how to pressure Israel
description: Despite the damning report presented on Thursday by the European Union foreign minister detailing violations of international law committed by Netanyahu's government, the 27 member states could not agree on whether to suspend the Association Agreement with Israel. The decision was postponed until mid-July.

description: European leaders thrashed out a trade strategy with the United States at a summit in Brussels, ahead of a July 9 tariff deadline. Germany is pushing for a conciliatory approach, while France is calling for a firm hand.

description: The progressive candidate is now the frontrunner in New York City's mayoral election, set for November, after defeating former state governor Andrew Cuomo, a symbol of the moderate local elite, in the Democratic primary.

description: Sensory tours at the Musée Rodin and Musée de l'Orangerie, mezzo forte concerts from the Orchestre Lamoureux, joyful splashing at Centquatre-Paris: More and more cultural venues in the French capital are offering activities for children under the age of two.
